# RESTup v1.3a.51230

Lightweight pure JavaSE/6 server provides a RESTful API to the console applications (hereinafter - services). 
Interaction with the server is performed according to the following General scheme:
- get a list of services (GET), to determine the URI of the service;
- create a job (POST) to selected service, to get the URI for the input files;
- send file(s) for the job (PUT);
- execute parameterized job (POST), to get the URI of the result files;
- get a list of result files (GET);
- get result file(s) (GET);
- delete the job and associated files (DELETE).
Server has an experimental WebDAV-based UI. An interface is a set of remote folders associated
with the corresponding service. The service contains subfolders for input and output files.
UI can be accesed via WebDAV clients: Windows Explorer, Gnome Nautilus etc.

Package include freeware-based examples (Linux/Windows) and Oracle-XE compatible PL/SQL client RESTful API. 
Examples require installed LibreOffice (4.x for Windows platform) & Tesseract OCR. 

Package contains:

\RESTup-RESTful_application_server_v1.3.pdf  ; documentation (sorry me - in Russian only)
\RESTupServer.jar                     ; server 
\ServerStart.bat                      ; starting script for Windows
\ServerStart.sh                       ; starting script for Linux
\Linux\                               ; config & examples for Linux                           
\Linux\Echo.sh                        ; echo service
\Linux\Office2x.sh                    ; transform office files
\Linux\RESTupConfig.xml             
\Linux\Tesseract-OCR.sh               
\Windows\                             ; config & examples for Windows
\Windows\Office2x.js 
\Windows\RESTupConfig.xml
\Windows\Tesseract-OCR.js
\Oracle\restup_web_server.sql         ; client for Oracle
\Source\RESTupServer.java
\Source\build.bat                     ; compile & build script
\Source\Help.txt                      ; help template for WebDAV users

